data.name: Classic Tomato Pasta Sauce
data.quickTastyDescription: A rich and flavorful tomato sauce that elevates any pasta dish with its robust taste and fresh ingredients.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add chopped onion and saut√© until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Stir in minced garlic and grated carrot, cooking for an additional 2 minutes until fragrant.
Add the canned whole tomatoes (including juice), sugar, salt, black pepper, and red pepper flakes (if using).
Bring the sauce to a simmer, then reduce heat to low and let it cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Taste and adjust seasoning as needed. Remove from heat and let cool slightly before blending if a smoother texture is desired.
Serve over your choice of pasta and garnish with fresh parsley.
data.modifiersForBase: Can be made vegan and gluten-free depending on pasta choice.
